transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm calling to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: I can take a look into that for you.

Speaker 2: What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 1: Myers, M-Y-E-R-S, 20659.

Speaker 2: Got it.

Speaker 1: So I pulled up your prescription here,

Speaker 2: and I do want to mention you're currently a VIP member with the Pfizer AGV.

Speaker 1: The moment we do cancel out these prescriptions,

Speaker 2: the doctor will actually delete the visit from the system,

Speaker 1: and you wouldn't be able to order.

Speaker 2: However, I can always switch you over to our every six-month plan.

Speaker 1: That way you can always call us when you need them

Speaker 2: or call us to delay it, and you retain access to the medication.

Speaker 1: Well, the medication doesn't work.

Speaker 2: Got it. No worries.

Speaker 1: And how have you been taking it, by the way?

Speaker 2: Are you taking it on an empty stomach?

Speaker 1: I take it like a turtle on the bottom, yeah.

Speaker 2: Got it, yeah.

Speaker 1: So as long as you're taking them as directed and they're not working for you,

Speaker 2: then Fortune probably isn't a good fit for you.

Speaker 1: So I'll go ahead and I'll just stop the orders with you.

Speaker 2: Other than that, you're all set to go.

Speaker 1: So it's canceled?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Have a good one. Bye-bye.
